url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dye, to pigmentate, to paint, to tincture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَبَغَ (ṣabaḡa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dye, pigment, paint, tincture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of صِبْغَة (ṣibḡa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ص ب غ (ṣ b ḡ). Compare Hebrew צבע (“to colour, paint, dye”), Aramaic צְבַע (ṣəbaʿ, “to dip, to dye”), Akkadian 𒍝𒁍𒌑 (/⁠ṣabû⁠/, “to soak, to bathe”), Ge'ez ጸብኀ (ṣäbḫä, “to dip”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23713","headword_ar":"صبْغٌ","root":"Sbg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, As, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogapN","text_ar":"صِبْغَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibagN","text_ar":"صِبَغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) or this is an inf. n., differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, As, L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibaAgN","text_ar":"صِبَاغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, O, Msb, K,) as some say, (O,) or this last is a pl. of the first, (O, * Msb,) [or] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaAgN","text_ar":"اَصْبَاغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, As, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used for colouring clothes"},{"kind":"text","text":"[& c.]: (TA:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibaAgN","text_ar":"صِبَاغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobigapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiygu","text_ar":"اَصَابِيغُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. pl. [i. e. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaAgN","text_ar":"اَصْبَاغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,] one says of a girl, or young woman, when one first takes her as a concubine, or when he first has her conducted to him as a bridge, (AZ, O,) or when one first marries her, (K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA laHadiyvapu AlSibogi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لَحَدِيثَةُ الصِبْغِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily she is one newly taken as a concubine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bride:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. alluding to the recent application of the dye of the hinnà]. (AZ, O, K.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^axa*otuhu biSibogi","text_ar":"مَا اَخَذْتُهُ بِصِبْغِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~amani","text_ar":"الثَّمَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^axa*ahu biSibogi vamanihi","text_ar":"مَا اَخَذَهُ بِصِبْغِ ثَمَنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not, take it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquire it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for its proper price,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its cost-price,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prime-cost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but for a high [or raised] price. (AZ, O, K. *) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies, (S, Mgh, O, Msb, TA,) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibaAgN","text_ar":"صِبَاغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) or the latter is pl. of the former, (S, O, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seasoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condiment, for bread, to render it savoury;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, TA;) particularly (Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is fluid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Adm","text_ar":"ادم"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as vinegar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and olive-oil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) [i. e. any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sauce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the bread is dipped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) so called because the bread is dipped in it, (Mgh, TA,) and coloured thereby: (Mgh:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibaAgN","text_ar":"صِبَاغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobigapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kavurati AlA^aSobigapu EalaY","text_ar":"كَثُرَتِ الاَصْبِغَةُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAy^idapi","text_ar":"المَايِدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fluid seasonings, were abundant upon the table."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in this sense, but not explained, in the K. (TA.) Hence, in the Kur [xxiii. 20],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSibogK liloA=kiliyna","text_ar":"وَصِبْغٍ لِلْا=كِلِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And a sauce for those that eat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, Msb, TA;) where it means, accord. to Fr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"olive-oil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to Zj,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the olive"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]; and Az prefers the latter explanation: (TA:) some read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSibaAgK","text_ar":"وَصِبَاغٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","As","S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n23714","headword_ar":"صَبَغٌ","root":"Sbg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in a horse, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the whole of the fetlock white, without its whiteness conjoining with that of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aHojiyl","text_ar":"التَّحْجِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23715","headword_ar":"صِبَغٌ","root":"Sbg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibogN","text_ar":"صِبْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}